# web2app — Convert web content to native iOS & Android apps

You have access to `web2app` (install: `git clone https://github.com/momomo-agent/web2app.git && cd web2app && npm install && npm link`).

## Usage

```bash
# URL → App
web2app init --url https://example.com --name "MyApp" --platform android

# HTML file → App  
web2app init --source ./index.html --name "MyApp" --platform both

# Web project → App
web2app init --source ./project/ --name "MyApp" --platform both

# With permissions
web2app init --source ./project/ --name "MyApp" --permissions camera,microphone,location --fullscreen --platform android

# Build
cd <project-dir> && web2app build --platform android
```

## Options

- `--name` (required): App name
- `--id`: Bundle ID (default: auto from name)
- `--url`: Remote URL to wrap
- `--source`: Local file or directory
- `--platform`: android | ios | both (default: both)
- `--permissions`: camera,microphone,location,storage,notifications
- `--fullscreen`: Enable fullscreen mode
- `--orientation`: portrait | landscape | any
- `--color`: Theme/status bar color (hex)
- `--icon`: App icon path (1024x1024 PNG)

## Prerequisites

- Android: JDK 17+, Android SDK
- iOS: macOS + Xcode 15+ + CocoaPods

## Output

- APK: `android/app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`
- iOS: Use `npx cap open ios` → Xcode archive
